### Challenge 2: [Brief descriptive title]

**What I was trying to do:**
I was attempting to use pivot_longer to lengthen the rec.spaces dataframe. Here is the code that I wrote to do so and the error that I received:
rec.spaces <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/regan008/DigitalMethodsData/main/raw/PlayAreabyType.csv")
pivot_longer(!type, names_to = "year")
> pivot_longer(!type, names_to = "year")
Error: object 'type' not found

This did not make sense because I knew that the column name "type" was correct and was listed in the rec.spaces data.


**What went wrong:**
I had forgotten to create a new dataframe at the start of the code. So when I asked the computer to overlook the type column and work on lengthening by year, it had no reference of where the type column was.

**My problem-solving process:**
1. I changed captialization on type to Type. This did not work.
2. I realized that I had not created a new dataframe to pass the lengthened data onto. I also realized that I had forgotten to use the pipe. 
